{"title":"api-gateway-introduction","date":"2018-10-23T00:00:00.000Z","slug":"api-gateway-introduction","tags":["api gateway"],"categories":["program"],"updated":"2018-10-23T00:00:00.000Z","content":"<h2 id=\"API-Gateway\">API Gateway<a href=\"post/api-gateway-introduction#API-Gateway\"></a></h2><h3 id=\"Foreword\">Foreword<a href=\"post/api-gateway-introduction#Foreword\"></a></h3><p>在非技术术语中，“网关或门是进入一个由墙围住的封闭空间的入口点。”同理，API网关是指位于防火墙或互联网后面<br>的服务的入口点。在微服务的世界中，网关坐镇于API前面，直接面向客户并进行反向代理。</p>\n<h3 id=\"Pros-and-cons-of-using-API-gateways\">Pros and cons of using API gateways<a href=\"post/api-gateway-introduction#Pros-and-cons-of-using-API-gateways\"></a></h3><ol>\n<li>好处：降低构建微服务的复杂性；微服务模拟与虚拟化</li>\n<li>弊端：在架构上需要额外考虑更多编排与管理；路由逻辑配置要进行统一的管理<ul>\n<li>网关会为端到端响应时间带来额外的延迟。</li>\n<li>潜在的性能瓶颈</li>\n<li>如果没有明智地选择网关，将会增加额外的运营开销和成本</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"Common-Gateways\">Common Gateways<a href=\"post/api-gateway-introduction#Common-Gateways\"></a></h3><p>Zuul</p>\n<p>Kong</p>\n","prev":{"title":"mq-introduction","slug":"mq-introduction"},"next":{"title":"kafka-build-with-docker-compose","slug":"kafka-build-with-docker-compose"},"link":"https://spaco.github.io/post/api-gateway-introduction/","toc":[{"title":"API Gateway","id":"API-Gateway","index":"1","children":[{"title":"Foreword","id":"Foreword","index":"1.1"},{"title":"Pros and cons of using API gateways","id":"Pros-and-cons-of-using-API-gateways","index":"1.2"},{"title":"Common Gateways","id":"Common-Gateways","index":"1.3"}]}]}